cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper investigates the use of genetic algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes new crossover operators to enhance the performance of genetic algorithms, which is a topic related to optimization and search algorithms (cs.DS). The experiments conducted in the paper involve solving the Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP), which is a well-known problem in the field of machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes selection strategies for the crossover operators, which is a topic related to robotics and control (cs.RO).
